text: Acestrorhynchus isalineae is a species of fish in the family Acestrorhynchidae. It was described by Naércio Aquino de Menezes and Jacques Géry in 1983. It is known from the Madeira River in Brazil. It reaches a maximum standard length of . ==References== Category:Acestrorhynchidae Category:Fish described in 1983
